<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,218,639]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,218,243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[274,418,218,243]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10428" refString="Sakai, K. (2011) Axioidea of the World and a Reconsideration of the Callianassoidea (Decapoda, Thalassinidea, Callianassida) Crustaceana Monographs, 13, 1 - 616. Available from: https: // decapoda. nhm. org / pdfs / 32288 / 32288. pdf (accessed 27 July 2017)" type="journal article">Sakai (2011)</bibRefCitation>
elevated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Manning &amp; Felder" authorityYear="1991" box="[527,693,218,243]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Callianopsinae">Callianopsinae</taxonomicName>
to family rank and added a second subfamily, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="2011" box="[1222,1433,218,243]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Neocallianopsinae">Neocallianopsinae</taxonomicName>
. The latter was said to differ from the former only in the absence of a ‘dorsal oval’ and cardiac sulci. Comparison of 
<taxonomicName authority="Lin, Komai &amp; Chan, 2007" authorityName="Lin, Komai &amp; Chan" authorityYear="2007" box="[151,706,290,315]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anovalis">
<emphasis box="[151,396,290,315]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianopsis anovalis</emphasis>
Lin, Komai &amp; Chan, 2007
</taxonomicName>
, 
<typeStatus box="[719,767,291,315]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">type</typeStatus>
and only species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="2011" box="[1004,1184,290,315]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Neocallianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1004,1184,290,315]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Neocallianopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with other species of the genus shows them to differ little; notably they share a similar rostrum, telson, uropod, maxilliped 3, chelipeds, and pleomere 6 with a pair of lateral teeth. The dorsal oval is difficult to define in these basal genera (unlike in Callichiridae). De 
<bibRefCitation box="[358,592,398,423]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref9502" refString="Saint Laurent, M. de (1973) Sur la systematique et la phylogenie des Thalassinidea: definition des familles des Callianassidae et des Upogebiidae et diagnose de cinq genres nouveaux. Comptes Rendus Hebdomadaires de Seances de l'Academie des Sciences, Paris, 277, 513 - 516. Available from: http: // gallica. bnf. fr / ark: / 12148 / bpt 6 k 5474901 n / f 589. image (accessed 23 August 2017)" type="journal article">Saint Laurent (1973)</bibRefCitation>
diagnosed the genus as having the ‘ovale bien délimité’ which was figured by 
<bibRefCitation box="[190,663,434,459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10980" refString="Schweitzer Hopkins, C. &amp; Feldmann, R. M. (1997) Sexual dimorphism in fossil and extant species of Callianopsis de Saint Laurent. Journal of Crustacean Biology, 17 (2), 236 - 252. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 193724097 X 00279" type="journal article">Schweitzer Hopkins &amp; Feldmann (1997)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald, 2015" authorityName="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald" authorityYear="2015" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Phaetoncalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauritana">
<emphasis box="[726,1024,434,459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Phaetoncalliax mauritana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10886" refString="Sakai, K., Turkay, M., Beuck, L. &amp; Freiwald, A. (2015 b) A collection of the Infraorder Callianassidea (Decapoda, Pleocyemata) with one new genus and five new species from the Eastern Atlantic off Mauritania (R / V Maria S. Merian cruise MSM 16 / 3 ' PHAETON'). Marine Biodiversity, 45 (1), 113 - 133. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 014 - 0227 - 2" type="journal article">Sakai, Türkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, otherwise similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[447,588,470,495]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[447,588,470,495]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has what appears to be a weak discontinuity between the gastric region and the rostrum (
<figureCitation box="[294,384,506,531]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,249,1937,1959]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,221,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,221,1884]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Callianopsis mauritana (Sakai, Türkay, Beuck&amp; FreiWald, 2015). A–E, holotype of Phaetoncalliax mauritana, F, paratypeof P.mauritana, SMF44111.A, carapacein lateral vieW; B,same in dorsalvieW;C, D, left pleopod,posterior vieW;E, same, anterior vieW; F, left and right pleopods 1 in situ, arroW points to pleuron 1 spine. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1196970/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). There would appear a continuum from well marked to undetectable in this variable character that is thereby unreliable as a generic or subfamily character. As we show below, all three genera recognised by 
<bibRefCitation box="[151,301,578,603]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10428" refString="Sakai, K. (2011) Axioidea of the World and a Reconsideration of the Callianassoidea (Decapoda, Thalassinidea, Callianassida) Crustaceana Monographs, 13, 1 - 616. Available from: https: // decapoda. nhm. org / pdfs / 32288 / 32288. pdf (accessed 27 July 2017)" type="journal article">Sakai (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, plus 
<taxonomicName authority="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald, 2015" authorityName="Sakai, Turkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald" authorityYear="2015" box="[375,1026,578,603]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Phaetoncalliax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[375,545,578,603]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Phaetoncalliax</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[556,1026,578,603]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref10886" refString="Sakai, K., Turkay, M., Beuck, L. &amp; Freiwald, A. (2015 b) A collection of the Infraorder Callianassidea (Decapoda, Pleocyemata) with one new genus and five new species from the Eastern Atlantic off Mauritania (R / V Maria S. Merian cruise MSM 16 / 3 ' PHAETON'). Marine Biodiversity, 45 (1), 113 - 133. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 014 - 0227 - 2" type="journal article">Sakai, Türkay, Beuck &amp; Freiwald, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
are subjective junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authority="de Saint Laurent, 1973" authorityName="de Saint Laurent" authorityYear="1973" box="[151,556,614,639]" class="Malacostraca" family="Callianassidae" genus="Callianopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,293,614,639]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="67">Callianopsis</emphasis>
de 
<bibRefCitation box="[332,556,614,639]" pageId="6" pageNumber="67" refId="ref9502" refString="Saint Laurent, M. de (1973) Sur la systematique et la phylogenie des Thalassinidea: definition des familles des Callianassidae et des Upogebiidae et diagnose de cinq genres nouveaux. Comptes Rendus Hebdomadaires de Seances de l'Academie des Sciences, Paris, 277, 513 - 516. Available from: http: // gallica. bnf. fr / ark: / 12148 / bpt 6 k 5474901 n / f 589. image (accessed 23 August 2017)" type="journal article">Saint Laurent, 1973</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the only genus, so subfamilies are superfluous.
</paragraph>
